Very excellent service from the owner and his staff.The staff which includes the owner's wife , son , daughter and the guys who are make the food are pleasant and respectful towards their customers  ( not like the people who work at a pizza parlor named J & R Pizza and Resturant which is a few blocks away from Kings Pizza ). The prices are a "steal " for only 7.00 dollars you can get a nice meal of baked ziti with a choice of chicken ( nice big pieces ) , nice thickly cut eggplant , Italian sausage or meatballs in it.Other places can charge 10.00 dollars for the same choices but the portions are smaller.If you like hot Heros than choose my personal favorite,  Chicken Cutlet or a nice Eggplant.If slices of pizza is your thing than give the vegetable slice a try or how about a slice of  Caesar Salad pizza or if you enjoy your slice spicy than give the Buffalo slice a try.

Italian pizza making is all too common in Brooklyn. They come in all shapes and sizes but few come with so much character. Every time we call them or go in person, their energy seems so positive and friendly that when the pizza comes to you, you don't mind paying a big tip. Family-run is always endearing but good pizza (& wings and garlic knots) seals the deal. So small that Michelangelo would have a hard time fitting in there but for the price, have found nothing better.
